            "content": "# Cortx CLI Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Build a schema-driven Rust CLI (\"cortx\") that stores Second Brain entities (tasks, projects, people, companies, notes, areas, resources) as Markdown files with YAML frontmatter, with a query language for filtering/aggregating, safe note editing primitives, and a doctor/lint system.\n\n**Architecture:** Hexagonal architecture with CLI layer (clap) -> domain/application layer -> repository trait -> Markdown adapter. Types are defined dynamically via a `types.yaml` schema config loaded at startup into a TypeRegistry. A small query language (parsed into an AST) evaluates predicates against frontmatter fields and body text. Note editing uses semantic operations (insert-after-heading, replace-block) instead of raw line edits.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust 2024 edition, clap (CLI), serde + serde_yaml (YAML), chrono (dates), walkdir (directory traversal), thiserror (errors)\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\ncortx/\n  Cargo.toml\n  types.yaml                         # Schema config for entity types\n  src/\n    main.rs                          # Entry point, CLI dispatch\n    config.rs                        # Load types.yaml, vault path resolution\n    error.rs                         # Unified error type\n    schema/\n      mod.rs                         # Re-exports\n      types.rs                       # TypeDefinition, FieldDefinition, FieldType\n      registry.rs                    # TypeRegistry (loads + validates types.yaml)\n      validation.rs                  # Validate frontmatter against schema\n    value.rs                         # Typed Value enum (String, Date, Array, Bool, etc.)\n    frontmatter.rs                   # Parse/serialize YAML frontmatter from .md files\n    entity.rs                        # Entity struct (id, type, frontmatter, body)\n    storage/\n      mod.rs                         # Repository trait\n      markdown.rs                    # MarkdownRepository implementation\n    query/\n      mod.rs                         # Re-exports\n      ast.rs                         # Query AST types (Expr, Op, Field, etc.)\n      parser.rs                      # Parse query string -> AST\n      evaluator.rs                   # Evaluate AST against Entity\n    cli/\n      mod.rs                         # CLI definition (clap App + subcommands)\n      create.rs                      # `cortx create` command\n      show.rs                        # `cortx show` command\n      update.rs                      # `cortx update` command\n      archive.rs                     # `cortx archive` command\n      delete.rs                      # `cortx delete` command\n      query_cmd.rs                   # `cortx query` command\n      meta.rs                        # `cortx meta` command (aggregations)\n      task.rs                        # `cortx task` subcommands (inbox, next, overdue, claim)\n      person.rs                      # `cortx person` subcommands (timeline, list)\n      company.rs                     # `cortx company` subcommands (people)\n      note.rs                        # `cortx note` subcommands (headings, insert, replace, patch)\n      doctor.rs                      # `cortx doctor` subcommands (validate, links)\n  tests/\n    common/mod.rs                    # Test helpers (temp vault setup)\n    schema_test.rs                   # Schema loading + validation tests\n    frontmatter_test.rs              # Frontmatter parse/serialize tests\n    value_test.rs                    # Value type tests\n    storage_test.rs                  # MarkdownRepository tests\n    query_parser_test.rs             # Query parser tests\n    query_evaluator_test.rs          # Query evaluator tests\n    cli_integration_test.rs          # En